HEADWORD: Poi
<hw>Po"i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A national food of the
Hawaiians, made by baking and pounding the kalo (or taro) root, and
reducing it to a thin paste, which is allowed to ferment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>
<-- also spelled <asp>poe</asp> -->

<p><ent>Poecile</ent>⟦br⟧
